              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "2BLGLVN"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".An 80 MeV 10 microAmp proton beam bombarded a",
                " 1 cm thick natural lithium target. Neutrons produced",
                " at 0 degrees were selected by a 1.6 m long conical",
                " iron collimator of 11 - 20 mm entrance - exit diame-",
                " ter. In addition, there were two halo collimators, 20",
                " cm long and 25 and 28 mm in diameter. The neutron in-",
                " tensity at 2.6 m from target was about 6.E+6 per sec."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The energies of the neutrons were determined",
                " with time-of-flight."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A scintillator telescope was used to detect",
                " the protons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A thin 0.1 mm scintillator of 3 cm diameter up-",
                " stream to the sample vetoed on charged particles in",
                " the neutron beam. 27 cm beyond the target a 12 cm dia-",
                " meter by 0.2 mm thick scintillator, with a 34 mm dia-",
                " meter hole to provide passage for the neutron beam,",
                " fired on charged particles. 1.25 m from the hydrogen",
                " target a 40 x 40 cm2 scintillator of 1 cm thickness",
                " acted as a proton energy detector. Protons of energy",
                " larger than 33 MeV were vetoed by another 40 x 40 cm2",
                " scintillator of 0.5 cm thickness, placed immediately",
                " after the E detector. The neutron detector was a",
                " 40 x 40 cm2 piece of scintillator of 5 cm thickness.",
                " A 56 mm hole was cut in each detector for the passage",
                " of the neutron beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "1-H-1(N,G)1-H-2,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "1-H-1(N,G)1-H-2,,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "1-H-1(N,G)1-H-2",
                        "target": "1-H-1",
                        "projectile": "N",
                        "process": "G",
                        "product": "1-H-2",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                "",
                " The np capture absolute cross section (14.2+-0.2 mu-b)",
                " was taken from current measurements in this Lab"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " From compiler: Later data are published at",
                " J,FBS,8,1,1990; but not at the same energy.",
                "  See 22229: 76.2 +- 2.1 MeV => 14.130 +- 0.19 mu-b"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".A liquid hydrogen target with a volume of 35 mm dia-",
                " meter and 5 mm thickness was placed 2.6 m from the",
                " neutron source. The target volume was limited by 6",
                " micrometer thick aluminized mylar windows."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Corrections were applied for neutron reactions in the",
                " proton detectors and for the finite efficiency of the",
                " neutron detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "N",
                "P"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The acceptance of the detector system and the effici-",
                " ency of the neutron detector were calculated with",
                " Monte Carlo codes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Also differential data, with respect to the azimuthal",
                " angle between the neutron and the proton were taken,",
                " and is presented in a figure."
              ]
            }
          ],
